        "title": "How do I inject two String values using Dagger 2?",
        "body": "<p>I'm trying to use Dagger 2 dependency injection and one of my requirements is that I be able to inject two string values into the created object.  The code below is my attempt to do that.  The values for brandName and modelNumber are never set in the created coffeeMaker (the printlns print null/null).<\/p>\n\n<p>Can anyone see what I'm doing incorrectly here?  <\/p>\n\n<p>Thanks<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>package com.so;\n\nimport dagger.BindsInstance;\nimport dagger.Component;\nimport dagger.Module;\nimport dagger.Provides;\n\nimport javax.inject.Inject;\nimport javax.inject.Named;\n\npublic class MyProblem {\n    interface ICoffeeMaker {\n        String getBrandName();\n        String getModelNumber();\n    }\n\n    class BrandXCoffeeMaker implements  ICoffeeMaker {\n        @Inject public String brandName;\n        @Inject public String modelNumber;\n        @Override public String getBrandName() { return brandName; }\n        @Override public String getModelNumber() { return modelNumber; }\n    }\n\n    @Module\n    class DaggerModule {\n        @Provides ICoffeeMaker provideCoffeeMaker() { return new BrandXCoffeeMaker();}\n    }\n\n    @Component(modules = DaggerModule.class)\n    interface CoffeeMakerComponent {\n        ICoffeeMaker getCoffeeMaker();\n\n        @Component.Builder\n        interface Builder {\n            @BindsInstance\n            Builder brandName(String brandName);\n            @BindsInstance\n            Builder modelNumber(String modelNumber);\n            Builder daggerModule(DaggerModule module);\n            CoffeeMakerComponent build();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public MyProblem() {\n        ICoffeeMaker coffeeMaker = DaggerMyProblem_CoffeeMakerComponent\n                .builder()\n                .brandName(\"Brand Name Here\")\n                .modelNumber(\"Model Number Here\")\n                .daggerModule(new DaggerModule())\n                .build()\n                .getCoffeeMaker();\n\n        System.out.println(coffeeMaker.getBrandName());\n        System.out.println(coffeeMaker.getModelNumber());\n    }\n\n    public static void main(String[] args){\n        new MyProblem();\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>(Edit: code formatting)<\/p>\n",
